            </nav>
        </div>
        <div class="row page-header col-md-12" style="margin-top:80px">
            <div class="col-md-3 img-responsive" align="center"><a href="Index"><img style="opacity:0.7; width:40%; height:auto;" src="~/Images/PeopleBank.jpg" /></a></div>
            <div class="col-md-6" align="center"><div class="col-md-12"><h5 style="font-family:'Lucida Sans', 'Lucida Sans Regular', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; width:100%; font-size:4vw;">The People's Bank</h5></div></div>
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
        </div>
        <strong><marquee style="border:BLACK 3px SOLID;font-family:'Times New Roman', Times, serif">||Always maintain $5000 as a minimum balance||If your balance goes below $5000, your credit score will reduce||You can open a new account only if the credit score is good|| </marquee></strong>
        <div class="panel panel-success">
            <!--Registration-->
            <div class="panel-heading">
                1) Registering an account
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>->Go to your nearest People's Bank store</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->Ensure you have the following details ready: SSN, Name, Date of Birth, Address, Phone Number and Email Id
                    </li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->You have to deposit a minimum of $5000 to open an account</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Bring an original and photocopy of your Passport/Driver's Licence</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Bring an original and photocopy of your SSN</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Ensure you receive a CustomerID and temporary password</li>
                    <br />
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-primary">
            <!--First time login-->
            <div class="panel-heading">
                2) First Time Login
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>->Enter the CustomerID and temporary password assigned to you by bank and press submit</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->Now enter your new password twice, the latter for confirmation
                    </li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->You will now be redirected to security questions page.</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->For first security question, choose one out of the ten available questions and enter answer</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->For second security question, write any question of your choice and enter an answer</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Click secure account. Your account is now secure</li>
                    <br />
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-success">
            <!--Transferring funds-->

            <div class="panel-heading">
                3) Transferring funds
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>->After logging in successfully, click on transfer funds</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->If you already have a beneficiary, click on the beneficiary
                    </li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Enter the amount you want to transfer</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Enter your login password again to transfer</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Hit send</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->If you want to add a new beneficiary, click on add beneficiary</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Enter beneficiarys account number and custom name</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>->Click submit</li>
                    <br />

                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-primary">
            <!--Forgot Password-->


            <div class="panel-heading">
                4) Forgot Password
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>->If you've forgotten your password, in the login page, click forgot password</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->You will be prompted to answer your security questions
                    </li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->Once you answer the questions correctly, you'll be redirected to change password page
                    </li>
                    <br />
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-success">
            <!--Forgot CustomerID-->


            <div class="panel-heading">
                5) Forgot CustomerID
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>->If you've forgotten your CustomerID, in the login page, click on forgot CustomerID</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->You will be prompted to write your SSN number
                    </li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->You will then have to answer your security questions
                    </li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->After answering questions correctly, you will now receive your CustomerID
                    </li>
                    <br />
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-primary">
            <!--Close Account-->



            <div class="panel-heading">
                6) Close Account
            </div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>->To close an account, ensure you have 0 balance left in your account</li>
                    <br />
                    <li>
                        ->Go to your nearest People's Bank store and request them to close the account
                    </li>
                    <br />
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
